00:11:43,495 --> 00:11:44,497
- Maybe you should
say, thank you, Carol,

257
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:46,665
for getting to my
sister's safely.

258
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:48,458
- Look at this guy!

259
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:49,835
Look at this guy!

260
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:51,295
Are you seriously just
gonna let him cut you off?

261
00:11:55,382 --> 00:11:57,927
(Dave grunting)

262
00:11:59,345 --> 00:12:02,263
- (laughing) No, no.

263
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:03,182
You know what?

264
00:12:03,265 --> 00:12:05,100
Let's try moving the recliner

265
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:06,810
and putting the
tree in the corner.

266
00:12:07,687 --> 00:12:09,188
I think that'll look great.

267
00:12:09,272 --> 00:12:10,730
- Me, too.
- Okay.

268
00:12:11,565 --> 00:12:13,067
(Dave grunting)
Careful. Got it?

269
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,568
- Out of my way, you putz.

270
00:12:14,652 --> 00:12:16,028
(horn honking)
Come on!

271
00:12:17,488 --> 00:12:19,573
(Dave panting)

272
00:12:19,657 --> 00:12:20,407
- Mm, no.

273
00:12:22,702 --> 00:12:23,952
- I will stop this car!

274
00:12:24,035 --> 00:12:25,287
I swear to everything holy,

275
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:27,247
I will stop this car
and come back there

276
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:29,542
and then you'll be in
a world of trouble!

277
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:32,628
(children grunting)

278
00:12:32,712 --> 00:12:33,462
- Perfect.

279
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:37,340
Okay, just start the
fire and we're done.

280
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:40,468
(light gentle music)

281
00:12:42,888 --> 00:12:45,598
(fire crackling)

282
00:12:58,028 --> 00:12:58,862
- Dad! Dad!

283
00:13:00,572 --> 00:13:01,865
Dad!

284
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:04,117
- Oh no! Dave!

285
00:13:04,202 --> 00:13:05,285
David! David!

286
00:13:07,747 --> 00:13:08,872
- Yeah, What?

287
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:10,790
- [Sandy] You forgot
to open the flue!

288
00:13:12,668 --> 00:13:13,835
- What?

289
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:16,255
- [Sandy] You forgot
to open the flue!

290
00:13:16,338 --> 00:13:18,257
(fire crackling)

291
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,633
(relatives chattering
indistinctly)

292
00:13:19,717 --> 00:13:21,218
- Get in with me.
Go ahead, girls.

293
00:13:21,302 --> 00:13:23,553
Okay, go ahead, girls. Okay.

294
00:13:23,637 --> 00:13:24,555
Hello, hello!

295
00:13:24,638 --> 00:13:27,432
(children cheering)

296
00:13:27,517 --> 00:13:28,683
- [Sandy] How was your trip?

297
00:13:28,767 --> 00:13:30,310
- Oh awful, seven
hours and 20 minutes.

298
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:32,103
That's the longest trip ever.

299
00:13:32,187 --> 00:13:34,690
(relatives chattering)

300
00:13:34,773 --> 00:13:36,775
- Are you okay?
- No, we're not hungry!

301
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:37,902
- What do you mean
we're not hungry?

302
00:13:37,985 --> 00:13:39,528
You can't tell me
when I'm not hungry.

303
00:13:39,612 --> 00:13:40,905
- I'm hungry!

304
00:13:40,988 --> 00:13:41,822
- I don't care, I don't
want you in that kitchen.

305
00:13:41,905 --> 00:13:42,990
They have enough to do in there.

306
00:13:43,073 --> 00:13:44,742
- What kind of
toilet paper you got?

307
00:13:44,825 --> 00:13:46,493
- Glad to see you.
- Hi!

308
00:13:46,577 --> 00:13:47,410
- So good to see you.

309
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:48,787
- Now, this is my orange soda.

310
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:50,580
I brought one for every day.

311
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:51,665
Look, got at my name on it,

312
00:13:51,748 --> 00:13:53,333
DM, Daryl McCormick.

313
00:13:54,668 --> 00:13:55,752
Okay, my name's on it.

314
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,672
- I ain't taking off my
shoes, my feet get cold.

315
00:13:57,755 --> 00:14:00,423
- I brought my footed pajamas.

316
00:14:00,507 --> 00:14:03,468
- I can't work with those
single-ply nonsense.

317
00:14:04,678 --> 00:14:06,388
- What kind of grown man
wears footie pajamas?

318
00:14:06,472 --> 00:14:08,515
- I like to be
comfortable, okay, Matt?

319
00:14:09,475 --> 00:14:11,560
- [Woman] Okay.

320
00:14:11,643 --> 00:14:12,393
Hi!

321
00:14:13,645 --> 00:14:14,813
- We're not handing out
free presents this year.

322
00:14:14,897 --> 00:14:16,857
- Oh no, I'm not-
- Remember?

323
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:19,818
- Taking my shoes off, not,
this isn't Communist China.

324
00:14:20,987 --> 00:14:23,780
Okay, come on, men,
let's storm the kitchen!

325
00:14:24,657 --> 00:14:27,033
- Hey, uh, do me a favor.

326
00:14:27,117 --> 00:14:28,410
Keys are in the jacket.

327
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:30,787
Go get my luggage,
would you? Bad back.

328
00:14:32,163 --> 00:14:32,957
- Okay.

329
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:37,293
- (sighing) Merry
Christmas, Mister Madison.

330
00:14:37,377 --> 00:14:39,087
- Merry Christmas,
Missus Madison.

331
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:46,303
("We Wish You a
Merry Christmas")

332
00:15:02,695 --> 00:15:04,947
- [Matt] So how are
you Mister Madison?

333
00:15:06,157 --> 00:15:07,742
- Well, I'm still alive.

334
00:15:14,332 --> 00:15:16,542
Oh, enough of this small talk.

335
00:15:16,625 --> 00:15:17,752
Let's turn on the TV.

336
00:15:20,712 --> 00:15:21,588
- Hey, Dad.

337
00:15:21,672 --> 00:15:22,673
- [Daryl] Yeah.

338
00:15:22,757 --> 00:15:24,883
- Isn't it true that
Santa Claus is real?

339
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:26,760
- Of course he's real.

340
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:28,887
- See, told you.

341
00:15:33,392 --> 00:15:34,727
- I really don't think
that making a batch

342
00:15:34,810 --> 00:15:36,395
or two of cookies
is gonna hurt us.

343
00:15:36,478 --> 00:15:38,688
- Cookies can be very harmful.

344
00:15:39,857 --> 00:15:41,317
- I'll tell you what.

345
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,735
We'll go to the gym on
December 26th and burn it off.

346
00:15:42,818 --> 00:15:44,027
What do you say?

347
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:45,903
- It's not just
the calories, Mom.

348
00:15:45,988 --> 00:15:47,197
There's also the
long term effects

349
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,865
of over-exposure to sugar,

350
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:51,285
which can change your
insulin sensitivity

351
00:15:51,368 --> 00:15:53,787
and you could get diabetes.

352
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:56,582
- I don't think we're in
any real danger of that.

353
00:15:56,665 --> 00:15:57,750
- Well, maybe not.

354
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,918
But it can also cause
tooth decay, anxiety,

355
00:16:00,002 --> 00:16:02,797
and a depressed feeling after
you crash from a sugar high.

356
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,923
No, thank you.

357
00:16:05,007 --> 00:16:07,133
- Kassandra, come
on, he's doing it!

358
00:16:07,217 --> 00:16:08,718
- Gotta go, Mom.

359
00:16:08,802 --> 00:16:10,303
Brandon's gonna prove
that Santa Claus is real.

360
00:16:11,347 --> 00:16:12,347
- Have fun!

361
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:15,725
- Here's part one
of my experiments

362
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,770
to prove that Santa
Claus is real.

363
00:16:17,853 --> 00:16:18,770
All right, I want you
guys to wait out here

364
00:16:18,853 --> 00:16:20,438
and witness me going
into the house.

365
00:16:20,522 --> 00:16:21,732
Everyone else is already inside.

366
00:16:21,815 --> 00:16:25,902
(light playful music)

367
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:27,403
- [Child In Red Cap]
What's that for?

368
00:16:27,487 --> 00:16:28,738
- In case I get I get
stuck in the chimney,

369
00:16:28,822 --> 00:16:29,907
my brothers can pull me out.

370
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,908
- Ah, smart.

371
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:34,870
- Here we go.

372
00:16:43,545 --> 00:16:44,838
- What's that for?

373
00:16:44,922 --> 00:16:46,173
- Brandon tied it
around his waist

374
00:16:46,257 --> 00:16:48,175
so if he gets stuck
we can pull him down.

375
00:16:48,258 --> 00:16:50,593
- Ah, smart!

376
00:16:50,677 --> 00:16:51,928
- Brandon's no dummy.

377
00:16:54,848 --> 00:16:56,433
- Come on Brandon,
you can do it.

378
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:00,103
- I'm stuck!

379
00:17:00,187 --> 00:17:01,020
Help, help!

380
00:17:02,522 --> 00:17:04,775
Help, I'm stuck, help, help!

381
00:17:04,858 --> 00:17:06,277
Help!
- Guys, pull!

382
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:09,112
(Brandon yelling)

383
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:19,707
- Cookies!

384
00:17:25,045 --> 00:17:26,045
- Cookies are ready.

385
00:17:26,838 --> 00:17:28,423
- Well, what about Brandon?

386
00:17:28,507 --> 00:17:29,633
- [Child Without A Hat] If
we don't get there fast,

387
00:17:29,717 --> 00:17:30,883
Dad and Uncle
Ben'll eat them all.

388
00:17:38,475 --> 00:17:42,062
- [Daryl] Mm, cookies.
We'll see about that.

389
00:17:42,938 --> 00:17:45,148
- Um, where's Brandon?

390
00:17:48,068 --> 00:17:49,318
- [Ben] Ooh!

391
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:52,155
- Uh, kids, have you
seen your cousin Brandon?

392
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:55,325
(light gentle music)

393
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:16,555
(Brandon yelling)

394
00:18:16,638 --> 00:18:18,307
(Matt yelling)

395
00:18:18,390 --> 00:18:21,518
(ornaments tinkling)

396
00:18:21,602 --> 00:18:22,352
- Brandon!

397
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,772
(sirens wailing)

398
00:18:25,855 --> 00:18:29,025
(gentle upbeat music)

399
00:18:39,703 --> 00:18:41,037
- Well, I hope you
guys are happy.

400
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,998
You could've killed Brandon!

401
00:18:43,082 --> 00:18:44,165
Go inside, all of you.

402
00:18:45,375 --> 00:18:46,710
And no cookies!

403
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:52,883
- I see your children
are misbehaving again.

404
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:54,802
- He's just a boy, Wesley.

405
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:59,557
- A halfwit boy who's gonna
grow up to be a halfwit man.

406
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:02,100
A lump of coal and
a good spanking,

407
00:19:02,183 --> 00:19:04,937
that's what you'd get
for Christmas were
I were your father.

408
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:07,438
I'd be doing you
a favor, too, boy.

409
00:19:14,028 --> 00:19:16,072
- Basement, shower, go.

410
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:19,325
And don't touch anything
on your way down.

411
00:19:21,578 --> 00:19:22,328
Dave!

412
00:19:24,748 --> 00:19:25,540
Dave!

413
00:19:30,045 --> 00:19:30,962
Have you seen Dave?

414
00:19:31,045 --> 00:19:32,213
- [Man] Where? All right.

415
00:19:32,297 --> 00:19:33,757
- Think he's around
here somewhere.

416
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:40,138
- Oh, oh, Mister
Madison, your shoes.

417
00:19:40,222 --> 00:19:41,723
- Just a little coffee please.

418
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:48,272
- Dave!

419
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:51,650
Dave?

420
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:53,193
- Huh, huh?

421
00:19:53,277 --> 00:19:54,570
What's going on?

422
00:19:54,653 --> 00:19:55,695
- What are you doing?

423
00:19:57,447 --> 00:19:58,532
- I cut a hole on the floor

424
00:19:58,615 --> 00:20:00,492
so I could go ice fishing.

425
00:20:00,575 --> 00:20:01,702
What does it look
like I'm doing?

426
00:20:01,785 --> 00:20:02,577
I'm taking a nap.

427
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:03,412
- Why?

428
00:20:04,537 --> 00:20:06,122
- Because I'm tired, Sandy.

429
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,082
- What do you have
to be tired about?

430
00:20:07,165 --> 00:20:08,750
I spent all morning cooking.

431
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,043
I've been following your father

432
00:20:10,127 --> 00:20:11,670
and his melting shoes
around the house with a mop.

433
00:20:11,753 --> 00:20:13,130
And I just helped
the fire department

434
00:20:13,213 --> 00:20:14,923
fish Brandon out of the chimney.

435
00:20:15,007 --> 00:20:16,342
- Chimney?

436
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:18,093
- Now I need you to
shovel the driveway.

437
00:20:18,177 --> 00:20:19,010
- Why?
- Because

438
00:20:19,093 --> 00:20:20,095
there's snow on it, David.

439
00:20:20,178 --> 00:20:21,053
- And?

440
00:20:21,137 --> 00:20:23,057
- And everybody's parked
out on the street,

441
00:20:23,140 --> 00:20:24,725
and we have a
perfectly big driveway.

442
00:20:24,808 --> 00:20:26,017
And if you just shovel it,

443
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:27,810
then everybody can put
in to the driveway.

444
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:29,187
- What do you care
if people are parked

445
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:31,357
in the street or the driveway?

446
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,773
- Get out of that bed!

447
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,360
- Fine!

448
00:20:35,443 --> 00:20:36,152
Fine!

449
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:47,455
(gentle light music)

450
00:20:47,538 --> 00:20:48,248
- Hey!

451
00:20:49,165 --> 00:20:50,167
Hey!

452
00:20:56,172 --> 00:20:58,175
Hey, how much for the driveway?

453
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:00,927
- 50 bucks.

454
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,138
- Ah, come on that's a little...

455
00:21:03,222 --> 00:21:04,682
All right.

456
00:21:04,765 --> 00:21:06,350
- You want the walk done, too?

457
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:10,353
- Well, yeah, the walk,
the porch, the driveway,

458
00:21:10,437 --> 00:21:12,188
the whole thing.

459
00:21:12,272 --> 00:21:13,107
- 60.

460
00:21:13,190 --> 00:21:14,107
- Ah, come on.

461
00:21:15,067 --> 00:21:16,402
- Come on, boys, lets go.

462
00:21:16,485 --> 00:21:17,277
- All right, fine.

463
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:18,445
60 bucks.

464
00:21:19,780 --> 00:21:22,323
- All right, get to
work, come on, go. Here.

465
00:21:26,202 --> 00:21:27,287
- Oh, you know what?

466
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:28,622
My neighbor's pushing 80.

467
00:21:29,748 --> 00:21:30,915
So do his for me, too.

468
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:32,625
- Okay.

469
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:33,918
- I mean, hey.

470
00:21:34,002 --> 00:21:34,585
It's the big guy's
birthday, right?

471
00:21:36,212 --> 00:21:37,213
- What is it?

472
00:21:38,215 --> 00:21:39,007
- Christmas.

473
00:21:40,008 --> 00:21:41,885
- Oh, Merry Christmas.

474
00:21:41,968 --> 00:21:44,847
- This one and the
one next door, okay.

475
00:21:44,930 --> 00:21:45,638
- Okay.

476
00:21:48,183 --> 00:21:51,478
- Oh, and, uh, hey, don't ring
the bell when you're done.

477
00:21:51,562 --> 00:21:53,438
I'll be watching
and I'll come out.

478
00:21:53,522 --> 00:21:55,190
- [Earl] Okay.

479
00:21:55,273 --> 00:21:58,152
Hey, come on slackers,
get your back into it.

480
00:22:00,112 --> 00:22:02,238
Go ahead and throw a whole
shovelful on your brother.

481
00:22:03,323 --> 00:22:06,535
(bright lively music)

482
00:22:09,578 --> 00:22:11,498
- [Carol] You need to
add 3/4 cup of sugar

483
00:22:11,582 --> 00:22:13,500
and a pinch of ginger.

484
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:15,752
- [Rachel] No, you only need
1/2 a cup of brown sugar

485
00:22:15,835 --> 00:22:19,547
and a dash, not a pinch,
a dash of cinnamon.

486
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:21,173
- Attention!

487
00:22:21,257 --> 00:22:22,592
Attention!

488
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:24,510
In five minutes, we
will finally be done

489
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:26,345
baking cookies for the year.

490
00:22:28,682 --> 00:22:29,473
- Psst.

491
00:22:30,392 --> 00:22:31,183
Psst!

492
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:34,103
- Dave, what are
you doing, buddy?

493
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:34,897
- Hey!

494
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:36,523
- Shut up, shut up!

495
00:22:36,607 --> 00:22:38,067
I need your room.

496
00:22:38,150 --> 00:22:40,068
- My room? What for?

497
00:22:40,152 --> 00:22:42,153
- Stop asking questions.

498
00:22:42,237 --> 00:22:45,948
Just keep Carol busy for about
an hour so I can take a nap.

499
00:22:46,032 --> 00:22:47,325
- I don't no.

500
00:22:47,408 --> 00:22:49,452
Sounds like we'll
get in trouble.

501
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:51,497
- Yeah, What's in it for us?

502
00:22:53,332 --> 00:22:55,083
- How about a free
home, free food,

503
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,127
and use of my big screen TV?

504
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:01,255
- Nah, I already got that.

505
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:02,840
- Yeah.

506
00:23:02,923 --> 00:23:06,720
- Fine, Christmas dinner,
you can have the turkey legs.

507
00:23:06,803 --> 00:23:09,430
It's my house, but you
can have the drumsticks.

508
00:23:14,393 --> 00:23:15,812
- Deal.

509
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:17,188
- Oh, we'll cover you.

510
00:23:17,272 --> 00:23:18,273
- All right.

511
00:23:18,357 --> 00:23:20,275
- We'll go right now.

512
00:23:23,112 --> 00:23:23,862
- These hot?

513
00:23:23,945 --> 00:23:25,405
- Hey, no touching.

514
00:23:26,573 --> 00:23:27,657
- What are you doing?

515
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:28,617
- I'm starving.

516
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:29,408
- Daryl, get out.

517
00:23:29,492 --> 00:23:30,785
- Matt, not now.

518
00:23:30,868 --> 00:23:32,245
No, no!

519
00:23:32,328 --> 00:23:33,705
- Matt, take it off.

520
00:23:33,788 --> 00:23:35,332
- I'm hungry.

521
00:23:35,415 --> 00:23:37,292
Hey wait, that's for
