But he loves his family.

1575
01:20:23,068 --> 01:20:24,487
That's what's important.

1576
01:20:27,157 --> 01:20:28,700
- Just all kinds of stuff.

1577
01:20:28,783 --> 01:20:29,868
Just clutter.

1578
01:20:29,952 --> 01:20:31,493
The gifts are too big,

1579
01:20:31,578 --> 01:20:32,912
and nobody really needs them.

1580
01:20:34,663 --> 01:20:36,332
- What can I say?

1581
01:20:36,415 --> 01:20:39,085
I like the gifts though.

1582
01:20:39,168 --> 01:20:40,795
- Matt?
- Huh?

1583
01:20:40,878 --> 01:20:42,672
Yeah, sure, hon.

1584
01:20:42,755 --> 01:20:45,008
- Now look, I've put
everybody's name in the hat.

1585
01:20:45,092 --> 01:20:46,718
We'll each draw out a name,

1586
01:20:46,802 --> 01:20:48,262
and that's the person you're
buying a gift for next year.

1587
01:20:48,345 --> 01:20:50,388
- I's Christmas day, Carol.

1588
01:20:50,472 --> 01:20:52,432
Do we really need to
worry about it now?

1589
01:20:53,600 --> 01:20:55,268
- Yes, when else
will all be together?

1590
01:20:55,352 --> 01:20:56,895
If we don't talk about it now,

1591
01:20:56,978 --> 01:20:58,187
it will never get done.

1592
01:20:58,272 --> 01:21:00,232
Daryl, you get to go first.

1593
01:21:04,152 --> 01:21:05,820
- I got my name,
Daryl McCormick.

1594
01:21:08,782 --> 01:21:10,408
- There you go, you can buy
yourself some orange soda,

1595
01:21:10,492 --> 01:21:11,743
and put your name on it.

1596
01:21:14,162 --> 01:21:14,955
- Or oven mitts.

1597
01:21:32,805 --> 01:21:33,848
- You feeling better, Grandpa?

1598
01:21:33,932 --> 01:21:36,517
- Ah, me? Sure, sure.

1599
01:21:36,602 --> 01:21:37,768
Takes a lot more than that

1600
01:21:37,852 --> 01:21:39,687
to knock your old
Grandpa off his game.

1601
01:21:41,982 --> 01:21:43,107
How'd you do this year?

1602
01:21:43,190 --> 01:21:44,692
You make out?

1603
01:21:44,775 --> 01:21:46,235
- Okay, I guess.

1604
01:21:46,318 --> 01:21:47,737
- Okay, you guess?

1605
01:21:47,820 --> 01:21:49,280
- I don't wanna complain.

1606
01:21:50,823 --> 01:21:52,825
- You mean you didn't get
everything you wanted?

1607
01:21:54,743 --> 01:21:55,912
Well, maybe next year.

1608
01:21:56,830 --> 01:21:57,747
- No.

1609
01:21:57,830 --> 01:21:58,790
- No!

1610
01:21:59,873 --> 01:22:01,250
- I was really good this year.

1611
01:22:01,333 --> 01:22:02,502
Really, I was.

1612
01:22:02,585 --> 01:22:05,005
And that's all I wanted.

1613
01:22:05,088 --> 01:22:08,550
And if Santa Claus didn't
bring me a dog this year,

1614
01:22:08,633 --> 01:22:09,800
why would he next year?

1615
01:22:09,883 --> 01:22:13,305
- Well, maybe your
parents for your birthday.

1616
01:22:13,388 --> 01:22:14,430
- They never will.

1617
01:22:15,682 --> 01:22:17,850
I just thought, if
I was good enough

1618
01:22:17,933 --> 01:22:19,768
and if I wanted it bad.

1619
01:22:20,728 --> 01:22:21,897
- Well, I'm sorry.

1620
01:22:21,980 --> 01:22:24,273
You know, I did as best I could.

1621
01:22:25,192 --> 01:22:26,860
- I still love you, Grandpa.

1622
01:22:26,943 --> 01:22:28,528
(Grandpa chuckling)

1623
01:22:28,612 --> 01:22:29,528
- What was that?

1624
01:22:29,612 --> 01:22:30,322
- What?

1625
01:22:30,405 --> 01:22:31,155
- That noise.

1626
01:22:32,073 --> 01:22:33,867
- I don't hear anything.

1627
01:22:33,950 --> 01:22:35,410
- From the basement that

1628
01:22:35,493 --> 01:22:37,787
whining, barking sound.

1629
01:22:37,870 --> 01:22:41,917
(building orchestral music)

1630
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:46,087
(bright orchestral music)

1631
01:22:46,170 --> 01:22:47,797
- [Kassandra] A
puppy! I got a puppy!

1632
01:22:47,880 --> 01:22:49,340
I don't believe this.

1633
01:22:49,423 --> 01:22:51,092
- Dad, what's going on?

1634
01:22:52,427 --> 01:22:53,345
- [Kassandra] I
don't believe this.

1635
01:22:53,428 --> 01:22:54,762
- [Grandpa] What's the big deal?

1636
01:22:54,845 --> 01:22:57,348
- You can't just buy her a
dog without our permission.

1637
01:22:57,432 --> 01:22:58,683
- Unbelievable.

1638
01:22:58,767 --> 01:23:00,435
- [Grandpa] You had a
dog when you were a kid.

1639
01:23:00,518 --> 01:23:02,062
Every kid should have a dog.

1640
01:23:02,145 --> 01:23:03,855
- Do you even know
what kind it is?

1641
01:23:03,938 --> 01:23:05,482
It's a, it's a, well it's,

1642
01:23:06,315 --> 01:23:07,233
I don't know.

1643
01:23:07,317 --> 01:23:09,068
I told the guy to get a big dog,

1644
01:23:09,152 --> 01:23:11,112
you don't want those
little rat dogs.

1645
01:23:11,195 --> 01:23:13,823
- This is a major
family decision, Dad.

1646
01:23:13,907 --> 01:23:15,408
A dog is a lot of work.

1647
01:23:15,492 --> 01:23:19,620
- Nonsense, you always
over-dramatize everything.

1648
01:23:19,703 --> 01:23:20,872
(dog yelping)

1649
01:23:20,955 --> 01:23:22,832
- [Carol] No, don't let him up

1650
01:23:22,915 --> 01:23:23,625
- [Kid] That knee, it's bad.

1651
01:23:23,708 --> 01:23:24,917
- [David] Get off there!

1652
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:26,753
(dog yelping)

1653
01:23:26,837 --> 01:23:28,463
Down, come here.

1654
01:23:28,547 --> 01:23:32,175
(talking over each other)

1655
01:23:32,258 --> 01:23:33,885
Get off there!

1656
01:23:33,968 --> 01:23:35,137
- [Sandy] David, do something!

1657
01:23:35,220 --> 01:23:37,930
- [David] I got him, I got him.

1658
01:23:39,973 --> 01:23:44,520
- [Sandy] Oh, my
china. (sighing)

1659
01:23:44,603 --> 01:23:45,855
- So, there you have it.

1660
01:23:45,938 --> 01:23:48,608
The Madisons got a
dog for Christmas.

1661
01:23:48,692 --> 01:23:50,652
Dave and Sandy may not
have wanted him at first,

1662
01:23:50,735 --> 01:23:51,903
but, throughout the years,

1663
01:23:51,987 --> 01:23:54,280
that dog brought a lot of love

1664
01:23:54,363 --> 01:23:55,740
into the Madison home.

1665
01:23:57,492 --> 01:23:59,035
Dave swore that he would never

1666
01:23:59,118 --> 01:24:02,622
have any of his or Sandy's
family over ever again.

1667
01:24:02,705 --> 01:24:03,623
Well, you know Dave,

1668
01:24:03,707 --> 01:24:05,833
next year he was
excited as ever.

1669
01:24:07,002 --> 01:24:08,795
It wasn't always easy.

1670
01:24:08,878 --> 01:24:10,338
One year, Dave got kicked

1671
01:24:10,422 --> 01:24:11,547
while trying to set up

1672
01:24:11,630 --> 01:24:13,758
a live reindeer display
in the front yard.

1673
01:24:13,842 --> 01:24:16,343
Then there was the time
he nearly froze to death,

1674
01:24:16,427 --> 01:24:17,970
while trying to prove to Sandy

1675
01:24:18,053 --> 01:24:20,848
that the ice was thick
enough for skating.

1676
01:24:20,932 --> 01:24:21,933
(chuckling)

1677
01:24:22,017 --> 01:24:24,810
Well, over time,

1678
01:24:24,893 --> 01:24:27,897
we gained a few new
Madisons and well,

1679
01:24:27,980 --> 01:24:29,482
we lost an older one.

1680
01:24:29,565 --> 01:24:33,152
But the family and their loving
dog always stayed together.

1681
01:24:34,362 --> 01:24:36,613
From all of us here
at Rockford, Michigan,

1682
01:24:36,697 --> 01:24:38,115
Merry Christmas,

1683
01:24:38,198 --> 01:24:40,160
and to all a good night.

1684
01:24:41,743 --> 01:24:45,332
(festive orchestral music)

